					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12365572#post-4335969</guid>
				<title>Author Post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12365572/scp-4318#post-4335969</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 20 Aug 2019 19:51:56 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Azmoeth Jikandia</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3895355</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Thanks to all who critiqued including <strong><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" >Uncle Nicolini</a></span></strong>!</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoilers</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Cheater&nbsp;:P</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>The SCP is told from the perspective of a &quot;demonic&quot; SCP Foundation that exists in some other universe. The actual SCP is just plain old H20 water. The banner furnish is supposed to be ironic (to the reader) anyway.</p> <p>Thanks for reading! Hope you enjoy!</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>Source for the banner at the top is&#8230;</p> <p><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/anomaly-classification-system-guide">http://www.scp-wiki.net/anomaly-classification-system-guide</a></p> <p>Thanks to <strong><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/woedenaz" >Woedenaz</a></span></strong> for making it!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
